replies.text: Isn't the whole point of the campaign to reach out to people who don't know the candidate too well and sell them on his merits? He's not doing a very good job of it
Well, not for me at least  :p

Do they really know their candidate?    Literally:    Day 1: There are no such accounts  Day 2: OK there are accounts but there's not much money    Day 1: Cut ties with Australia/US  A week later: Who am I to cut ties with Australia/US?    Reputation for anti-corruption --admires Marcos, supported Binay. Now he'll send Binay to jail.    China: enter bilateral talks, give up claim to West Philippine Sea; now he'll go over there and plant a flag. OK.    There is so much more of that.    This is stuff they castigate other candidates for but which they are completely blind to when it's Duterte.
